                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>did not that letter come safe to hand.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am sorry to trouble you with this<lb/> small matter; but if I am\n                to attend<lb/> to any business for you it is better that<lb/> we should have all\n                items, properly ac-<lb/>counted for. I will communicate<lb/> with you hereafter in\n                regard to send-<lb/>ing books here to be disposed of &amp;<lb/> in the meantime will\n                do what I<lb/> can to procure subscribers for you, in<lb/> this section, my time is\n                not so much<lb/> occupied but that I can attend<lb/> to any thing you may desire\n                here!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Occident to <persName>Mr Marcuson</persName> and<lb/> myself\n                comes to hand! <persName>W. M.</persName> I trust<lb/> will content himself here\n                tho' from<lb/> all I have seen of him his great<lb/> fault is being unsettled!\n                    <sic>he</sic> is a<lb/> frequent visitor at my house and</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sn01q6d/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
